<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="110" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
The 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="section" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="section" section="Secundae" species="section">section Secundae</taxonomicName>
was originally suggested to belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="subg. Poa" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="subg." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P." order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus" subGenus="Poa">P. subg. Poa</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2419340" author="Soreng, RJ" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" pagination="507 - 528" refId="B33" refString="Soreng, RJ, 1991a. Systematics of the &quot;Epiles&quot; group of Poa (Poaceae). Systematic Botany 16 (3): 507 - 528, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2419340" title="Systematics of the &quot; Epiles &quot; group of Poa (Poaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2419340" volume="16" year="1991 a">Soreng 1991a</bibRefCitation>
), but, in subdividing the genus into more subgenera based on our plastid phylogeny (
<bibRefCitation author="Gillespie, LJ" journalOrPublisher="Aliso" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" pagination="420 - 434" publicationUrl="https://doi.10.5642/aliso.20072301.33" refId="B12" refString="Gillespie, LJ, Archambault, A, Soreng, RJ, 2007. Phylogeny of Poa (Poaceae) based on trnT-trnF sequence data: major clades and basal relationships. Aliso 23: 420 - 434, https://doi.10.5642/aliso.20072301.33" title="Phylogeny of Poa (Poaceae) based on trnT-trnF sequence data: major clades and basal relationships." url="https://doi.10.5642/aliso.20072301.33" volume="23" year="2007">Gillespie et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
), the section was moved to subg. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Stenopoa">Stenopoa</taxonomicName>
(Dumort.) Soreng &amp; L.J. Gillespie. We subsequently discovered that the set of plastid 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Secundae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Secundae" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Secundae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genotypes resolved in a clade with three European diploid species with 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Nn</emphasis>
genotypes, but the nrDNA genotypes of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Secundae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Secundae" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Secundae</taxonomicName>
were like those of subg. 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Secundae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Stenopoa">Stenopoa</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Ss</emphasis>
) (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3906/bot-1611-28" author="Cabi, E" journalOrPublisher="Turkish Journal of Botany" pageId="15" pageNumber="116" pagination="404 - 415" refId="B6" refString="Cabi, E, Soreng, RJ, Gillespie, LJ, 2017. Taxonomy of Poa jubata and a new section of the genus (Poaceae). Turkish Journal of Botany 41: 404 - 415, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3906/bot-1611-28" title="Taxonomy of Poa jubata and a new section of the genus (Poaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3906/bot-1611-28" volume="41" year="2017">Cabi et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/njb.01507" author="Soreng, RJ" journalOrPublisher="Nordic Journal of Botany" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" pagination="513 - 538" refId="B42" refString="Soreng, RJ, Gillespie, LJ, Consaul, LL, 2017. Taxonomy of the Poa laxa group, including two new taxa from Arctic Canada and Greenland, and Oregon, and a re-examination of P. sect. Oreinos. Nordic Journal of Botany 35 (5): 513 - 538, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/njb.01507" title="Taxonomy of the Poa laxa group, including two new taxa from Arctic Canada and Greenland, and Oregon, and a re-examination of P. sect. Oreinos." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/njb.01507" volume="35" year="2017">Soreng et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
and results presented above). The apparently ancient reticulate origin of the group, along with its odd morphology within 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Poa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, now leads us to raise the section to the rank of subgenus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
